{"lemma":"آلِفٌ","slug":"آلِفٌ","root":"#.ل.ف","root_slug":"_-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آلِفٌ","root":"لفو","pos":"V","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1063","n1064","n1065"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D9%84%D9%90%D9%81%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of آلْف (ʔālf, “elf (mythical or fantasy creature)”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from English elf."},"ipa":["/ʔilf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1063","headword_ar":"اَلْفٌ","root":"Alf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain round number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) [namely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thousand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is of the masc. gender: (T, S, Msb, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapu A=laAfK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةُ ا=لَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Three thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"], not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAva A=laAfK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَ ا=لَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^alofN waAHidN","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَلْفٌ وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is one thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"], not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidapN","text_ar":"وَاحِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alofN A^aqoraEu","text_ar":"اَلْفٌ اَقْرَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A complete thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T, S,) not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroEaA='u","text_ar":"قَرْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) it is not allowable to make it fem.: so say IAmb and others: (Msb:) or it is allowable to make it fem. as being a pl.: (T:) or, accord. to ISK, it is allowable to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi A^alofN","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ اَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~araAhimu A^alofN","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّرَاهِمُ اَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These dirhems are a thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K; *) and Fr and Zj say the like: (Msb:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lufN","text_ar":"ا=لُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to three, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=laAfN","text_ar":"ا=لَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,) applied to a number from three to ten, inclusively, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uluwfN","text_ar":"اُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,) used to denote more than ten; (T;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aAfu","text_ar":"الاَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^alafu","text_ar":"الاَلَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is used by poetic licence for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=laAfu","text_ar":"الا=لَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by suppression of the [radical]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","T","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1064","headword_ar":"اـِلْفٌ","root":"Alf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifahu","text_ar":"اَلِفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,] He"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with whom one is familiar, sociable, companionable, friendly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amicable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"he"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom one keeps or cleaves;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a constant companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"associate; a mate; a fellow; a yoke-fellow; one who is familiar, &c., with another"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^al~afN","text_ar":"مُوَلَّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliyfN","text_ar":"اَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, K;) which is an act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifahu","text_ar":"اَلِفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) as is also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifN","text_ar":"ا=لِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifN","text_ar":"اَلِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliyfN","text_ar":"اَلِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the female is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofapN","text_ar":"اـِلْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofN","text_ar":"اـِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) both of these signifying a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with whom thou art familiar, &c., and who is familiar, &c., with thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and the fem. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifN","text_ar":"ا=لِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifapN","text_ar":"ا=لِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofN","text_ar":"اـِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=laAfN","text_ar":"ا=لَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M;) which is also pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifN","text_ar":"اَلِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliyfN","text_ar":"اَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaAy^ifu","text_ar":"اَلَايِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulafaA='u","text_ar":"اُلَفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifN","text_ar":"ا=لِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ul~aAfN","text_ar":"اُلَّافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=laAfN","text_ar":"ا=لَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoSaArN","text_ar":"اَنْصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASirN","text_ar":"نَاصِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and so, (M, TA,) in my opinion, [says ISd,] (M,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uluwfN","text_ar":"اُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwdN","text_ar":"شُهُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhidN","text_ar":"شَاهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) though some say that it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofN","text_ar":"اـِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifapN","text_ar":"ا=لِفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAlifu","text_ar":"اَوَالِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifaAtN","text_ar":"ا=لِفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fvlaAnN A_ilofiY","text_ar":"فثلَانٌ اـِلْفِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliyfiY","text_ar":"اَلِيفِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is my constant companion or associate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] (T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~ati AlA_ilofu A_ilaY A_ilofi","text_ar":"حَنَّتِ الاـِلْفُ اـِلَى اـِلْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female mate yearned towards the mate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazaEa AlbaEiyru A_ilaY A=laAfihi","text_ar":"نَزَعَ البَعِيرُ اـِلَى ا=لَافِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel yearned towards his mates"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ul~aAfN","text_ar":"اُلَّافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=laAfN","text_ar":"ا=لَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) is said by IAar to mean Persons"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keep to the large towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cities."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uluwfN","text_ar":"اُلُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ii. 244 is said by some to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofN","text_ar":"اـِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lifN","text_ar":"ا=لِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": but by others, to signify \"thousands.\" (Bd, L, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ayori","text_ar":"الطَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAlifu","text_ar":"اَوَالِفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The birds that keep to Mekkeh and the sacred territory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamaAmi","text_ar":"الحَمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAlifu","text_ar":"اَوَالِفُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Domestic pigeons."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","M","T","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n1065","headword_ar":"اَلِفٌ","root":"Alf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilofN","text_ar":"اـِلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  As some say, (O,) it also signifies A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the letters of the alphabet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aliyfN","text_ar":"اَلِيفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) Ks says that, accord. to the usage of the Arabs, it is fem., and so are all the other letters of the alphabet; [and hence its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alifaAtN","text_ar":"اَلِفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] but it is allowable to make it masc.: Sb says that every one of them is masc. and fem., like as is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vein lying in the interior of the upper arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the fore arm:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) so called as being likened to an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the two are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^alifaAni","text_ar":"الاَلِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any kind of things: (K, TA:) as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for it denotes the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"number one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}